    "description": "Processes with NO command line set, excluding the always-empty system kernel processes (PID 0 = System Idle, PID 4 = System). Memory-resident injected code, doppelgänger / hollowed processes, and certain kernel-launched workers often present with a missing or empty Cmd field in pstree because the PEB has been tampered with or never populated. Treat as anomaly worth correlating against the same PID in pslist / dlllist / malfind.",
